<span id="freeTextContainer8438105928722650224">*3.5 stars<br/><br/>A very cute romance, steeped in magical realism and seasoned with Southern charm. This was picked as the first reading selection for a new book club at my local library--probably as counterpoint to the heavier reads of the &apos;other&apos; book club. <br/><br/>Josey Cirrini, 27 and still living at home under her wealthy mother&apos;s thumb, takes solace in her hidden closet of indulgent sweet treats. But one day she discovers something else in that closet...something that may help her &apos;get a life.&apos; Some fun s</span>
  <span id="freeText8438105928722650224" style="display:none">*3.5 stars<br /><br />A very cute romance, steeped in magical realism and seasoned with Southern charm. This was picked as the first reading selection for a new book club at my local library--probably as counterpoint to the heavier reads of the 'other' book club. <br /><br />Josey Cirrini, 27 and still living at home under her wealthy mother's thumb, takes solace in her hidden closet of indulgent sweet treats. But one day she discovers something else in that closet...something that may help her 'get a life.' Some fun supporting characters help flesh out this quickly-read story.</span>
